This paper deals with machine learning algorithms and statistical analysis in neuroimaging research, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on training complex machine learning algorithms and increasing statistical power in association studies. The second likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper deals with analyzing magnetic resonance images of the brain. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses modeling confounders as unknown, latent variables. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with analyzing brain scans. The fifth likely category is cs.ST (Statistics), as the paper discusses confounding bias and dataset harmonization.
